From: Li RongQing <roy.qing.li@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 3 Jun 2013 22:11:16 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 049/223] cxgb3: Correct comparisons and calculations using
 skb->tail and skb-transport_header
Patch-mainline: v3.11-rc1
Git-commit: 15dd16c233b6d5ceea3a00f18d7c42902d0ac6b6 (partial)
References: bsc#909577 FATE#317550

This corrects an regression introduced by "net: Use 16bits for *_headers
fields of struct skbuff" when NET_SKBUFF_DATA_USES_OFFSET is not set. In
that case skb->tail will be a pointer whereas skb->transport_header
will be an offset from head. This is corrected by using wrappers that
ensure that comparisons and calculations are always made using pointers.

Cc: Simon Horman <horms@verge.net.au>
Signed-off-by: Li RongQing <roy.qing.li@gmail.com>
Reviewed-by: Simon Horman <horms@verge.net.au>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: David Chang <dchang@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/chelsio/cxgb4/sge.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/chelsio/cxgb4/sge.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/chelsio/cxgb4/sge.c
@@ -1293,7 +1293,7 @@ static inline unsigned int calc_tx_flits
 
 	flits = skb_transport_offset(skb) / 8U;   /* headers */
 	cnt = skb_shinfo(skb)->nr_frags;
-	if (skb->tail != skb->transport_header)
+	if (skb_tail_pointer(skb) != skb_transport_header(skb))
 		cnt++;
 	return flits + sgl_len(cnt);
 }
